        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>
          The Brettl-Hupfers Ski & Sports Club is dedicated to fostering a community of outdoor enthusiasts who share a passion for skiing, snowboarding, hiking, canoeing, and other outdoor activities. We believe in the power of friendship, adventure, and the great outdoors to bring people together.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Our Location</h2>
        <p>
          Located in beautiful Bartlett Village, New Hampshire, our clubhouse is strategically positioned just two miles from Attitash/Bear Peak Ski Area and within easy reach of 10 other ski areas in the region. This prime location makes us the perfect base for year-round outdoor adventures in the White Mountains.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Our Community</h2>
        <p>
          We're a diverse group of people united by our love for outdoor sports and the camaraderie that comes from sharing adventures together. Whether you're an experienced skier or just starting your outdoor journey, you'll find a welcoming community here.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Year-Round Activities</h2>
        <p>
          While skiing and snowboarding are at the heart of our winter activities, we embrace all seasons with hiking, canoeing, and other outdoor sports. Our calendar is filled with events that bring members together and create lasting friendships.
        </p>
